Fix 5 showstopper bugs — learning system was fundamentally broken

Honest post-mortem: the system was collecting data but every core
meteorological signal path was broken. Predictions were essentially
random, so the learning loop was training on garbage.

BUG 1 — PRESSURE DATA WAS NULL FOR EVERY STATION
The cron requested vars=pressure and read pressure_value_1d, but
every other endpoint in the codebase correctly requests altimeter
and reads altimeter_value_1. Result: pressure was null for all 29
stations, making the entire pressure gradient analysis return 0.
North flow detection, frontal passage, thermal suppression — all
non-functional. Fixed by matching the pattern used everywhere else
and adding normalizeToMb() to convert inHg to mb.

BUG 2 — HISTORY ARRAY WAS REVERSED
Redis LPUSH stores newest-first. Scoring functions assumed oldest-
first (history[0]=oldest). Result: tempDrop=newer-older was always
negative during cold fronts. Wind shift detection was inverted.
Speed ramp detection saw decreases as increases. Every trend-based
indicator was backwards. Fixed by sorting recentSnapshots
chronologically before passing to the learning cycle.

BUG 3 — UTC VS MOUNTAIN TIME IN THERMAL SCORING
Vercel runs in UTC. now.getHours() returned UTC hours. But thermal
peak windows [10,16] are 10AM-4PM Mountain Time. At noon MT (UTC
18), scoreThermal gave NEGATIVE points. At 4AM MT (UTC 10), it
gave BONUS points. Thermal predictions were inverted. Fixed by
adding toMountainHour() using Intl.DateTimeFormat with fallback.

BUG 4 — PRESSURE ALTITUDE BASELINE WAS WRONG
PRESSURE_ALTITUDE_BASELINE was 7.5 (designed for station pressure)
but altimeter readings are already altitude-corrected. The baseline
should be 0. Set to 0.

BUG 5 — redisCommand SWALLOWED ALL ERRORS
No error checking for HTTP failures, rate limits, or Upstash
errors. If the free tier limit was hit, all operations silently
returned null. Added HTTP status check, JSON error check, and
try/catch with console.error logging.

Additional hardening:
- Batch appendAccuracyLog into single LPUSH (saves N-1 commands)
- Add diagnostic output (pressure check, MT hour, snapshot order)
- Fix backfill to also request altimeter and use Mountain Time
- Clean up duplicate expectedSpeed unpacking in verifyPredictions

IMPORTANT: After deploying, re-run backfill to retrain weights
with correct data: /api/cron/collect?action=backfill&days=3
